<TITLE> Pabna Textiles College on rushed vacation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, May 26 (bdnews24.com)  Demonstrations over fee hike by students who besieged teachers forced Pabna Textile Engineering College to declare summer vacation four days ahead of schedule. Students on Wednesday staged a protest rally and obstructed teachers including the principal demanding reduction of the session fee hiked more than three times recently. The administration increased the fee from Tk 1,520 to Tk 4,070 effective from this year. Later police came in and freed the teachers. Additional police were deployed on the campus. The college was declared shut for one month. Acting principal Shib Shankar Chakrabarti told bdnews24.com: "The college was scheduled to go on vacation on May 30. But it has been declared closed before that date due to the situation." The college will open on June 29, he added. bdnews2
